Do NOT invent function signatures, API contracts, types, component props, or data structures that are not specified in the skill files or CLAUDE.md.

If something is ambiguous, stop and ask rather than guessing.

If a type is defined in a skill file, use EXACTLY that type — do not add fields, remove fields, change names, or alter return types.

If a function signature is specified, use EXACTLY that signature — do not add parameters, change parameter types, or rename anything.

Never fabricate metrics, version numbers, package names, or API capabilities. If you don't know something, say so.
